object.customQuery:
SELECT Coverage.CoverageId as CoverageId, Coverage.PolicyKey as PolicyKey, 
Coverage.CoverageSystemId as CoverageSystemId, Coverage.CoverageCd as CoverageCd 
FROM dbo.Coverage Coverage 
join dbo.policystats_stg ps
on Coverage.CoverageSystemId = ps.policyref
where Coverage.RowEffEndDt='9999-12-31 00:00:00.000'
and Coverage.RiskId is NULL
ORDER BY Coverage.CoverageSystemId

order by risksystemid, policykey,

else Risk.locationid end, riskid

fields.name: o_RiskId
fields.expression:
IIF(INSTR(PolicyKey1,'U')=1 or CoverageCd='MinPrem',
IIF(ISNULL(RiskId1), '0', RiskId1),
IIF(ISNULL(RiskId), '0', RiskId))

object.customQuery:
select CoverageId as CoverageId,
PolicyKey as PolicyKey,
CoverageSystemId as CoverageSystemId,
CoverageCd as CoverageCd,
RiskId as RiskId
from
(
SELECT distinct Coverage.CoverageId as CoverageId, 
Coverage.PolicyKey as PolicyKey, 
Coverage.CoverageSystemId as CoverageSystemId, 
Coverage.CoverageCd as CoverageCd, 
Coverage.RiskId as RiskId,
rank() over (partition by coverage.PolicyKey, coverage.CoverageSystemId, coverage.CoverageCd, coverage.RiskID, coverage.CoverageStatus order by coverage.CoveragePremiumAmt, coverage.coverageDesc, coverage.CoverageId) as CoverageItemCd
FROM dbo.Coverage
JOIN dbo.policystats_stg ps 
ON coverage.coveragesystemid = ps.policyref
where RowEffEndDt='9999-12-31 00:00:00.000'
) sub
where CoverageItemCd = 1
order by CoverageSystemId
